"'''Red Sky, Blue Flame'''" is a short story by [[Elaine Cunningham]], published in [[Star Wars Gamer 7]] in [[2001]]. It is set in a [[Chiss/Legends|Chiss]] [[Syndic Mitth'raw'nuruodo training academy|military training outpost]] in the [[Rata Nebula/Legends|Rata Nebula]], a few years before the events of the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]].

"Red Sky, Blue Flame" tells the story of how [[Jagged Fel]] proved his command abilities to [[Shawnkyr Nuruodo]] and his other Chiss comrades, how he came to acquire the distinctive scar across his forehead, and also how the Chiss came to trust the [[Fel dynasty|Fel family]].

==Plot summary==
Fourteen [[Standard year/Legends|year]] old [[Jagged Fel]] attends a [[Syndic Mitth'raw'nuruodo training academy|Chiss military academy]] on the frozen [[Planet/Legends|world]] of [[Rhigar/Legends|Rhigar]]. The academy is attacked by [[Pirate/Legends|pirates]]. Fel uses his [[Nssis-class Clawcraft|clawcraft]], ''[[Blue Flame]]'', to lure the pirates into a clever trap of his devising, earning the respect and admiration of his [[Chiss/Legends|Chiss]] peers, who would not usually consider treating a [[Human/Legends|human]] outsider as an equal.

==Continuity==
The place of ''Red Sky, Blue Flame'' in ''[[Star Wars]]'' chronology is problematic. Several internal references strongly imply that it occurs very soon after ''[[Vision of the Future]]'' in [[19 ABY/Legends|19 ABY]], and that was almost certainly the author's intent, but the story apparently describes the [[Death/Legends|death]] of [[Kres'ten'tarthi|Stent]], who is alive in [[Timothy Zahn]]'s subsequent novel, ''[[Survivor's Quest]]'', set in [[22 ABY/Legends|22 ABY]].<ref name="TERC" />

In ''Red Sky, Blue Flame'', [[Jagged Fel|Jag Fel]] was fourteen [[Standard year/Legends|years]] old.<ref name="TERC" /> ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' states that Jag Fel was [[Reproduction/Legends|born]] in [[7 ABY/Legends|7 ABY]], establishing that the story takes place in [[21 ABY/Legends|21 ABY]].

When the discrepancy became apparent, [[LucasBooks]] editor [[Sue Rostoni]] initially suggested that the story ought to be relocated to occur after ''Survivor's Quest''.<ref name="Boards">{{SWBoards|url=thread.jspa?threadID=93010&start=5430|thread=Sue Rostoni on the StarWars.com Message Boards|author=[[Sue Rostoni]]|nobackup=1}}</ref> However, the novel ''[[Dark Nest I: The Joiner King]]'' appears to abandon an important part of Rostoni's fix, the proposed equation of Jag's brothers [[Davin Fel|Davin]] and [[Chak Fel|Chak]], and some fans feel that it is easier to explain Stent's survival and Jag's age than to force the backstory of ''Red Sky, Blue Flame'' to fit around the events of ''Survivor's Quest''.

''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'' states that the ''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]'' resolved the problem by clearly stating that Stent survived the attack on [[Rhigar/Legends|Rhigar]], but the entries in the encyclopedia relating to this are still vague in their depiction.<ref name="TERC" />

